  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Feeding minds and tummies of 230 children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Murakaza school is a beacon of hope for 230 children and their families living in a slum outside of Bujumbura, Burundi. As well as teaching them literacy and life skills, they are mentored to integrate the national school system to continue their education. An important development was when the school began to offer a daily nutritious meal - often the only meal that the children will receive a day. In addition, the school grows its own food, also helping to employ local people.</narrative>
  </description>
